content: Brody Garrison Brink is a combination of three surnames as a full name. Brody is a first name of Scottish origin, which means "ditch" or "muddy place." Garrison is a surname of English origin, which means "a fortified place" or "a garrison." Brink is a surname of Dutch and German origin, which means "edge" or "border." All three surnames have different meanings and origins, and when combined, they create a unique and distinctive full name.
